description.plain:
Written by Thurston on vacation in California in summer ‘89, it was chosen as the opening song of Sonic Youth’s album Goo (1990) and as the third and final single off the record.

There are several versions of this song available:
* A version on the Kool Thing single  with alternative ending, entitled “Rock n Roll Heaven”;
* Two demo versions, one complete and one edited, in the Goo Demos;
* Two live versions, one recorded in 11/3/1990, in Irvine, California, available on the Dirty Boots single and one recorded between August and September, 1991, available on the video “The Year Punk Broke”.

